 BY BAMIDELE FAMOOFO In a move to realign its business with the present realities in Africa’s largest economy, construction giant, Julius Berger Plc, is set to commission its new cashew plant located in Epe, Lagos State. The Company in 2020 had hinted that it is taking a foray into the agriculture sector as a way of boosting its revenue sources. The Company, on September 23, 2020, announced to the Market the Board approval of the diversification opportunity for the Company in Agro-processing. A statement signed by Julius Berger Company Secretary, Mrs. C.E Madueke disclosed: “In 2020 the Board of Directors approved the Company’s first diversification case and its implementation has already commenced. Julius Berger’s success is well founded on our leading technical expertise, innovation with a proven record of reliably delivering construction solutions to the highest standards and all these are being deployed to its agro-processing activities.” Julius Berger subsequently advised its shareholders of the development through its 2020 Annual Reports and Consolidated Financial Statements. “Julius Berger is pleased with and indeed excited about its progress with this initiative. Julius Berger reiterates that our diversification direction would support the continued success of the Julius Berger Group in the future and align with the strategic objectives of the Government to stimulate value creation in Nigeria,” the Company told the Nigerian Exchange Limited in a statement. 